    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-01-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="580" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                <head>No. 581.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Davis</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Baker</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>
                            <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-01-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 18, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 199.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Adverting to previous correspondence upon the
                        subject, I have now to inclose for your information copy of a note from the
                        British minister here, of the 15th instant, concerning the custody of ships’
                        papers when in the ports of Venezuela.<note n="*" xml:id="d580fn1">For
                            inclosure see document No. 280, <ref target="#pg_491">page
                            491</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN DAVIS,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
